Description: Fragment of lip, neck and flattened handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, unclear number. Name Alexandros. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum MGR P.16249.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (10)
